Cancer Buddy is your go-to tool to organise your cancer journey. Living with cancer often requires constant and repetitive need to manage symptoms, medicine intake, and making appropriate lifestyle choices, which can get messy and stressful. Our application aims to ease such a burden off of patients.
One App to do it all
With functions to address the various needs of cancer patients all incorporated into ONE application, Cancer Buddy hopes to streamline the cancer journey management.
Set reminders to alert yourself when it is time to take your medicine. Use our tool to keep track of your medicines, add personalised notes about your medicine intake.
Keep track of the presence and severity of your symptoms. Data visualisation techniques help you see the trend of your symptoms over time to give deeper insights into your recovery process.
Stay conscious of your food intake, access guidelines recommended for cancer patients along with sample recipes and diet plans.
Boost your immunity by staying active through exercise. Access various categories of exercises, open up the video and simply do along.
Keep up to date and connect with others going through similar experiences. Share and receive support from other cancer patients.
SIDE TO SIDE LUNGE WITH PUNCHES
Keep left foot on step.Step up with right leg by not putting on step and bend knees to bring towards chest. Step down by right and then left foot. Step up and repeat.
Stand with feet together and arms at side. Jump by raising your arms and separating legs to side. Land on your toes with arms raised above head.
Jump side to side by keeping legs together and hands on your waist. Land by slightly bending kness and on the balls of your feet.
Quick step ups with alternate legs.

Keep feet together. Then right knee up and kick. Then balance on left leg and keep right leg behind with hands on floor and bring back left leg to make a plank. Step left leg to make lunge and kick with right leg again. Make plank again and continue.
Face forward. Step right leg back and bend to a lunge. Punch with left then right arm. Come to center and do the same but to the left side now and keep on alternating.
Make a squat by keeping legs shoulder width apart. From the squat, jump up with bith hands above and land on a squat.
Lay down and keep core tight. Kepp hips on the ground and raise right leg and left arm and stretch. Then lower down and alternate sides.
Stand straight and stretch spine. Inhale and reach down and touch the toes by keeping knees straight and hold. Exhale and reach up and stretch by keeping arms above.
Stand straight and stretch spine. Keep hands above and after inhaling bend backwards as much possible. Hold and come back to normal position while exhaling.

Keep feet more than shoulder width apart with arms stretched so they are parallel to ground. Bend to the right side and touch right feet with right arm and look towards left hand. Come back to normal position and bend alternate side.
Lay down and bring your left knee forward and keep right leg stretched back. The elongate spine and look up. Keeep hold for 30 seconds and then relax and alternate sides.
Stand straight and sit in chair position.Lift right leg over left and tuck your foot and bring right arm under left arm. Sit back and hold for 20 seconds. Come back to standing and alternate sides.
Stand straight and balanced. Bend right leg at the knee and keep the foot on left inner thigh. Stretch your body and hold for 20 seconds. Relax and change side.
Keep feet more than shoulder width apart. Extend arms to side and relax shoulders. Turn left leg 90 degress and bend into lunge. Turn head to left and look over the fingers. Alternate sides.
Sit on mat with knees bent and feet flat. Lean back so that neck is above ground and stretch your arms legs forward above ground level. Stretch and hold for 30 seconds. Relax and repeat.
Stand shoulder width apart with dumbbel in each hand and arms on the side. Squeeze biceps and lift dumbbell to shoulder level and then low down. Repeat.
Stand shoulder width apart with dumbbell in each hand and arms on the side. Bend a little and raise your arms sideways to shoulder level and then lower down.

Stand straight and keep right leg behing and bend forward a little. Bend your right arm inside while holding dumbbell and stretch it by straightening arms toward the ground. Repeat and alternate sides.
Keep palm on chair to hold your bodyweight and slide forward until your behind is off the chair. Lower your body and elbows to 45 to 90 degrees. Push back until arms are straight and repeat.
Bring torso forward and bend a little while holding dunbbells. Bring elbows up to keep arms parallel to ground and straighten it to extend the arms back. Come back to start position and repeat.

Lay down and bend your knees and only keep upper arms on ground while holding dumbbells. Straighten your arms up by pushing dumbbells over the chest and stretch. Bring down ars back to ground and repeat.
Keep only palms and toes on ground and stretch body. Pull right knee to chest as much possible and then put it back and bring left knee to chest. Alternates running knees.
Keep only forearms and toes on the ground and inhale. Keep your spine straight so that hips arent uplifted or psoture is not wrong. Hold that position and then relax.
Stand straight with feet hip width apart. Raise on your toes and squeeze your calves. Lower your heels down and repeat.
Keep feet hip width apart and cross your left leg behind right leg by taking a step back. Bend your knees into a lunge and return to starting position. Alternate legs.
Keep a box behind you. Put right foot on the box and bend your knees until left thigh is parallel to ground. Come back to start position and repeat.
Stand shoulder width apart with arms on each side with dumbbells. Bend knees forward and go to squat position and return to standing position.
Stand straight. Then take big step forward with left leg and keeping weight on left leg bend so that left thigh is parallel to floor. Come back to start position and repeat. Switch legs.

Stand with feet hip width apart. Step right leg more to the side and bend its knee until right thigh is parallel to ground and left leg is full straight. Return to normal position and then switch sides.
Stand straight. Then take big step backward with left leg and keeping weight on right leg bend so that right thigh is parallel to floor. Come back to start position and repeat. Switch legs.

. Lie down with knees bent and arms flat on the side with palms facing ground. Lift hips from the ground until shoulders, hips and knees are in a straight line. Hold the bridge for 3 seconds then relax. Repeat

Keep neck and back straight. Take right arm and lift to touch left side of head. Pull the head towards left side and stretch the neck by holding for 20 seconds. Sraighten your neck and then alternate sides.

Stand tall with right foot few inches forward of left foot and right toes lifted. Bend left knee slightly and keeping body weight on left leg stretch the back muscles of right leg. Hold for 20 seconds then switch sides.
Stand straight and shift weight to left leg. Bend back your right leg by holding your right foot by right hand. Touch your butt with the right foot and hold for 30 seconds. Relax and change legs.
Lay down with knees bent. Bring right knee to chest with help of both hands and then stretch your left leg until it fully touches the ground. Hold it for 20 seconds, relax and switch legs.

Lay down with knees bent. Bring right ankle to left knee making 4 position. Reach through the bent knee and grasp the back of left leg and bring it to the chest. Relax and hold this position for 20 seconds, then switch sides.

Kneel on the ground with top of feet on the mat and sit up straight. Place your fingertips on your lower back. Now slowly look up and lean backwards by stretching first right and then left hand back wards until you touch your heels. Once heels are secured, shift and balance full body weight and stretch your body for 20 seconds. Then exit by bringing hands back to lwer body slowly and getting back to start position. Repeat.

Lay down flat facing the ground. Place palms under the shoulder and bend elbows. Inhale and lift your chest until arms are straight and loop up while stretching your back. Hold the position and then exhale and relax to starting position. Then repeat.

Kneel on the ground and then bow down forward by extending your arms forward and touching forehead to the ground. Relax and hold this position and stretch your spine and arms for relief. Slowly return back to start position and repeat once again.

They help to boost the immune system. Blueberries are not only packed with vitamin C, fibre, and manganese but are also rich in cancer-fighting antioxidants. One research revealed that blueberries are associated with inhibition of cancer cell proliferation.

Apples are rich in polyphenols, substances that may have anti-inflammatory, anti-cancer, and tumour-fighting properties. One study even suggested that the polyphenols in apples inhibit the growth of breast cancer cells.

During cancer treatment, patients may encounter certain side-effects like nausea. Ginger can help to relieve nausea and essentially calms the stomach.Gigner also contains antioxidants and anti-inflammatory compounds.
Carrots contain beta-carotene, a potent antioxidant that helps to boost the immune system and promote brain, skin, eye and lung health.

Leafy greens contain a lot of vitamins and minerals that improve our overall health, which protects patients’ bodies from other diseases, improves recovery, and increases your resistance to treatment side-effects.
They contain nutrients such as potassium, vitamin B, and omega-3 fatty acids which are known to be good for the heart.
Walnuts provide antioxidants. Some researchers also found that consuming walnuts could change the bacteria in our digestive system in a way that suppresses colon cancer.
Beans contain many cancer-fighting agents like phytates, which help slow down certain cancers, protease inhibitors that help slow tumour development, and manganese that protects cells from damage.
Mushrooms help to boost the immune system.

The curcumin in turmeric has antioxidant properties that may reduce inflammation. In addition, some reports also mentioned that curcumin could slow down cancer progression, protect healthy cells, and make chemotherapy more effective.
Food Safety: Foods to limit or avoid
It is important to cut back on foods that may aggravate your health
Examples include alcohol and foods high in saturated fats, sodium, and sugars.
Besides these foods, avoid the following would also help to reduce the risk of food poisoning:
● Uncooked cold cuts; even pre-cooked luncheon meats must be reheated until ‘steaming hot’
● Unpasteurised milk, or cheese made from unpasteurised milk
● Ready-made or deli-salad with egg, ham, chicken, or seafood as it is not practical to reheat them
● Raw seafood or meat, such as sushi and sashimi
